Part 1 | Module 0: The Pro Se Onboarding Ritual
Goal: To stabilize the case and protect your rights in the "Blackout Period" (the first 72â€“168 hours after losing representation).

1. The Document Audit (The "Source Code" Check)
Before you file anything, you must know what the court thinks is happening.
- The Docket Scan: Download the complete docket. Identify the very next deadline.
- The "Substitution of Counsel": Ensure the court has your current contact information. If you don't receive the mail, you lose by default.
1. The "Motion for Extension of Time" (Buying Breath)
Courts generally grant a one-time "grace period" when an attorney withdraws.
- The Script: "Pro Se Litigant [Your Name] respectfully requests a 30-day stay or extension to secure new counsel or familiarize themselves with the procedural posture of the case."
- The Ritual: This isn't just a filing; it's your first act of sovereignty. You are telling the court: I am here, and I am paying attention.
1. The Emotional Firewall
- The Rule of 24: Never respond to opposing counselâ€™s emails in under 24 hours. They will use your lack of representation to bait you into emotional, legally damaging admissions.
